        "*Log real GDP (copper) and log real consumption (sky blue) from 1947Q1 to\n",
        "2019Q4. Both series are clearly non-stationary in levels: they trend upward\n",
        "without bound, and their deviations from any fixed reference point do not\n",
        "revert. Yet they track each other with a consistency that suggests more than\n",
        "coincidence — the gap between the two series is far more stable than either\n",
        "series itself.*\n",
        "\n",
        "The visual makes two things plain. First, both series are I(1): they trend\n",
        "upward throughout the sample with no tendency to revert to a fixed level.\n",
        "Formal ADF and KPSS tests, which students have applied extensively in previous\n",
        "chapters, confirm this. We report them again here for completeness."
